Faculty profile




Marco   LevoratoAssociate ProfessorDEGREE:Ph.D., 2009, University of PadovaRESEARCH AREAS: Artificial Intelligence and Machine LearningNetworks and Distributed SystemsStatistics and Statistical TheoryRESEARCH INTERESTS: Dr. Levorato's research focuses on the analysis and design of the next generation wireless networks, mobile health care networks and smart energy grids. His research makes use of concepts and tools from stochastic modeling, signal processing, graph theory and optimization theory to create novel approaches to the analysis, control and optimization of complex systems.

CONTACT INFORMATION:

